sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091107

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_C0051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:description: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:source: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:note:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS.
Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091104
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:description: This promoter is a modified version of the Mnt promoter that is also responsive to LacI. The promoter should be repressed by Mnt repressor. It should also be repressed by LacI, and in the absence of Mnt repressor, should be induced by IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: Robert Cool
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:source: This part comes from the Mnt promoter and the LacI promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:note: Mnt repressor binds as a tetramer to two half-operator sites. Introduction of a LacI binding site between the Mnt promoter -10 sequence and the start site for transcription should allow for repression by LacI. Accordingly, the hybrid promoter was designed by 1) Remove all bases of mnt promoter 3??? to -10: gagtcgtattaattt will be replaced by tgtgtggaattgtga, and 2) Position lacI binding site (composed of an inverted repeat) from the lacI regulated promoter (R0010) immediately 3??? to truncated mnt promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:description: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:source: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:note:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_C0072
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mnt repressor (strong) from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: crackdots
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:note: wild type dimeric repressor from enterobacteriophage p22 with dissociation constant of 2.5*10^-12.
sequence was translated with the E.Coli K12 codon usage table, and nucleotides 95-97 was changed from AAT to AAC to avoid the cut site GAATTC (94-99).
Identification of Functionally Important Residues in the DNA Binding Region of the MNT Repressor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:description: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:author: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:source: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.igem:note: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
